<section id="improvised-iron" class="content-panel" aria-labelledby="improvised-title">
    <h2 id="improvised-title"><span aria-hidden="true">🛠️</span> Improvised Iron Cheat Sheet</h2>
    <p>No gym? No problem. Use these universal swaps to keep the gains flowing when equipment is light.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>No Barbell?</strong> Use heavy dumbbells. If you don't have those, use resistance bands anchored to a door.</li>
        <li><strong>No Bench?</strong> Do floor presses. Lie flat on the ground and press—it actually protects your shoulders.</li>
        <li><strong>No Cable Machine?</strong> Swap cable flyes and pushdowns for resistance bands or standard dumbbell equivalents.</li>
        <li><strong>No Pull-Up Bar?</strong> Do inverted rows under a sturdy table, or heavy dumbbell bent-over rows.</li>
    </ul>
</section>
